You can avoid the ConcurrentModificationException by using a try-catch block and re-adding the element back to the list if the exception is thrown. Something like this: 

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        List<Integer> numbers = new ArrayList<>();
        numbers.add(1);
        numbers.add(2);
        numbers.add(3);
        numbers.add(4);
        numbers.add(5);

        for (Integer n : numbers) {
            if (n % 2 == 0) {
                try {
                    numbers.remove(n);
                } catch (Exception e) {
                    numbers.add(n);
                }
            }
        }

        System.out.println(numbers);
    }
}

